# Grouped GEMM shapes (2Dx2D variant: variable contraction dim K)
# src[M, total_K] * wei[total_K, N] -> dst[G, M, N]
#
# Format: --grouped=1:<num_groups>:<group_sizes> MxK:KxN
# Where:
#   1            - variable dim is index 1 of src (the contraction dim)
#   num_groups   - number of groups/experts
#   group_sizes  - '+'-separated list of per-group K sizes (sum must == total_K)
#   M            - output rows
#   K            - total contraction dim (sum of group_sizes)
#   N            - output cols
#
# Note: --reset after batching this file to avoid leaking --grouped

# uniform per-group K
--grouped=1:4:8+8+8+8
64x32:32x32
--grouped=1:8:8+8+8+8+8+8+8+8
64x64:64x64

# Unbalanced groups
--grouped=1:3:2+6+8
32x16:16x24
--grouped=1:4:10+20+30+40
64x100:100x32

# Empty/zero-sized groups
--grouped=1:6:0+1+2+0+3+0
24x6:6x20
--grouped=1:4:8+0+16+8
32x32:32x32

# Single group
--grouped=1:1:8
16x8:8x12
